1
00:00:01,376 --> 00:00:02,793
narrator: NOW THE STORY 
OF A WEALTHY FAMILY

2
00:00:02,793 --> 00:00:03,836
WHO LOST EVERYTHING

3
00:00:03,836 --> 00:00:06,172
AND THE ONE SON 
WHO HAD NO CHOICE

4
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:08,633
BUT TO KEEP THEM ALL TOGETHER.

5
00:00:13,554 --> 00:00:16,557
IT'S "ARRESTED DEVELOPMENT."

6
00:00:18,976 --> 00:00:22,313
- ANOTHER SETBACK FOR THE 
ONCE-PROMINENT BLUTH FAMILY

7
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:25,650
AS THEIR FROZEN BANANA STAND, 
A NEWPORT BEACH LANDMARK,

8
00:00:25,650 --> 00:00:27,110
BURNS TO THE GROUND.

9
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:30,405
A DELICIOUS WHODUNIT AFTER THIS.

10
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:31,781
[door buzzer buzzing]

11
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,741
narrator: 
A WEEK BEFORE THE FIRE,

12
00:00:33,741 --> 00:00:36,452
MICHAEL BLUTH WAS TRYING TO SAVE 
THE BLUTH COMPANY,

13
00:00:36,452 --> 00:00:38,246
BUT HIS FATHER 
WAS MAKING IT DIFFICULT.

14
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:40,331
- I NEED THE FLIGHT RECORDS, 
DAD.

15
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:42,708
I'M TRYING TO FIND SOME MONEY 
FOR THE FAMILY.

16
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:44,169
- THERE'S ALWAYS MONEY 
IN THE BANANA STAND.

17
00:00:44,169 --> 00:00:47,338
I AM HAVING A LOVE AFFAIR 
WITH THIS ICE CREAM SANDWICH.

18
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:48,798
YOU WANT SOME? 
YOU WANNA TAKE A BITE?

19
00:00:48,798 --> 00:00:49,799
- PLEASE, PLEASE. 
- COME ON, TAKE A BITE.

20
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:51,801
- THE S.E.C. 
HAS LOCKED UP OUR FUNDS.

21
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,136
THESE GUYS 
AREN'T MESSING AROUND.

22
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:55,155
- NO TOUCHING.

23
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:57,057
- SO I NEED YOU TO TELL ME,

24
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:58,849
WERE YOU TAKING VACATIONS 
IN THE JET?

25
00:00:58,849 --> 00:01:00,185
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE HIDING 
FROM ME?

26
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:02,603
- [scoffs] I HAVEN'T HAD 
A VACATION IN YEARS.

27
00:01:02,603 --> 00:01:04,772
THIS IS MY VACATION.

28
00:01:04,772 --> 00:01:06,149
I'M EXERCISING.

29
00:01:06,149 --> 00:01:07,233
I'M SLEEPING WELL.

30
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,818
- YOU'RE DOING TIME.

31
00:01:08,818 --> 00:01:11,171
- I'M DOING THE TIME OF MY LIFE.

32
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:13,114
- WHAT'S UP, PUMPKIN?

33
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:15,366
- HEY, T-BONE.

34
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,368
YEAH, 
T-BONE'S MY ROOMMATE.

35
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:20,705
- OH. 
- [whispering] HE'S A FLAMER.

36
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:21,706
T'S CHECKING OUT TODAY.

37
00:01:21,706 --> 00:01:22,998
- YEAH.

38
00:01:22,998 --> 00:01:25,960
- WELL, I GUESS EVERY VACATION'S 
GOTTA COME TO AN END.

39
00:01:29,964 --> 00:01:32,425
- YOU JUST MADE A FOOL OUT OF 
YOURSELF IN FRONT OF T-BONE.

40
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:36,304
ANYWAY, I WANT YOU TO GIVE HIM 
A JOB AT THE COMPANY: SALES.

41
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:37,597
- I'M NOT GONNA DO THAT. 
- WHY NOT?

42
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:38,723
- WELL, BECAUSE... 
- BECAUSE HE'S A FLAMER?

43
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:39,890
- WE DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY.

44
00:01:39,890 --> 00:01:41,058
- BECAUSE I TOLD YOU THAT 
IN CONFIDENCE.

45
00:01:41,058 --> 00:01:42,059
- YOU DON'T SEEM TO UNDERSTAND

46
00:01:42,059 --> 00:01:44,019
THAT I'M RUNNING 
THIS COMPANY NOW, DAD,

47
00:01:44,019 --> 00:01:46,772
AND I NEED THE FLIGHT RECORDS, 
AND I'M GONNA GET THEM

48
00:01:46,772 --> 00:01:48,358
WITH OR WITHOUT YOUR HELP.

49
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:52,820
- ALL RIGHT. 
- NO TOUCHING.

50
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:54,405
- I GOT SOMETHING WE CAN TRY, 
ALL RIGHT?

51
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,656
IT'S A LITTLE RISKY.

52
00:01:55,656 --> 00:01:57,032
- PLEASE.

53
00:01:57,032 --> 00:01:58,075
- OPEN UP.

54
00:01:58,075 --> 00:02:01,871
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN, ABOUT...

55
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:04,957
narrator: WHILE GEORGE SR. 
WAS LOSING A ROOMMATE,

56
00:02:04,957 --> 00:02:08,503
GEORGE MICHAEL WAS HAVING A HARD 
TIME ADJUSTING TO HIS NEW ONE.

57
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,338
- GET UP. GET UP. GET UP. 
GET UP. GET UP.

58
00:02:10,338 --> 00:02:11,922
- I'M UP.

59
00:02:11,922 --> 00:02:14,509
- OKAY, WE ARE JUST ABOUT 
ASS TO ANKLES BACK HERE, MAEBY.

60
00:02:14,509 --> 00:02:19,054
DO YOU WANNA HOP ON YOUR 
COUSIN'S LAP THERE, PLEASE?

61
00:02:19,054 --> 00:02:22,392
- WHOA, BUMPY ROAD AHEAD.

62
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:23,768
- [sighs]

63
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:27,021
[singing] 
GOT NOTHIN' ON BUT LOVE NOW.

64
00:02:27,021 --> 00:02:30,316
narrator: SO HE ADDRESSED 
HIS PROBLEM HEAD-ON.

65
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:32,360
- DAD, I WANNA WORK MORE HOURS 
AT THE BANANA STAND.

66
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,069
- WOW.

67
00:02:34,069 --> 00:02:36,239
HUH, WELL, THAT'S GREAT.

68
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:39,116
YOU KNOW, I USED TO BE 
JUST LIKE YOU WHEN I WAS A KID.

69
00:02:39,116 --> 00:02:40,368
I USED TO LOVE IT THERE.

70
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:45,498
- [GEORGE] IT'S GONNA BE OUR 
BEST SUMMER EVER, MIKEY.

71
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:47,041
- WELL, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

72
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:50,295
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU A PROMOTION. 
WELCOME ABOARD, MR. MANAGER.

73
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:52,505
- WOW, I'M MR. MANAGER.

74
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,674
- WELL, MANAGER. 
WE JUST SAY "MANAGER."

75
00:02:54,674 --> 00:02:57,927
AND YOU CAN HIRE AN EMPLOYEE 
IF YOU NEED ONE.

76
00:02:57,927 --> 00:02:59,220
- DO YOU THINK I NEED ONE?

77
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:01,180
- DON'T LOOK AT ME, 
MR. MANAGER.

78
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:03,349
- RIGHT. 
IT'S UP TO ME NOW.

79
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:04,892
I'M MR. MANAGER.

80
00:03:04,892 --> 00:03:06,727
- MANAGER. 
WE JUST SAY...

81
00:03:06,727 --> 00:03:09,021
-I KNOW, BUT YOU JUST-- 
- IT DOESN'T MATTER WHO.

82
00:03:16,737 --> 00:03:19,240
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I EXPECTED.

83
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,991
WHAT'S GOING ON?

84
00:03:20,991 --> 00:03:22,243
THIS IS EXACTLY 
WHERE THE TWO OF YOU WERE

85
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:23,828
WHEN I LEFT THIS MORNING.

86
00:03:23,828 --> 00:03:25,705
- IS NOBODY GONNA EVEN TRY 
TO GET A JOB?

87
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,707
- I HAVE A JOB, MICHAEL. 
- YEAH?

88
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:29,292
- IT'S CALLED 
SUPPORTING MY HUSBAND.

89
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,586
- WELL, YOU CERTAINLY 
HAVEN'T BEEN SHOPPING.

90
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:32,753
THE ONLY THING I FOUND 
IN THE FREEZER

91
00:03:32,753 --> 00:03:34,714
WAS A DEAD DOVE IN A BAG.

92
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,173
- YOU DIDN'T EAT THAT, 
DID YOU?

93
00:03:36,173 --> 00:03:38,593
'CAUSE I'VE ONLY GOT A COUPLE 
DAYS LEFT TO RETURN IT.

94
00:03:38,593 --> 00:03:41,804
DIED RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE 
OF A SHOW.

95
00:03:41,804 --> 00:03:43,223
- DO YOU WANT A CAGE FOR THAT?

96
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,225
- NO. 
I'M A MAGICIAN.

97
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,893
[dove cooing]

98
00:03:47,893 --> 00:03:49,937
[bells jingles]

99
00:03:49,937 --> 00:03:51,231
[cooing stops]

100
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:54,234
WHAT IS YOUR RETURN POLICY, 
BY THE WAY?

101
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,818
- NOT THAT I HAVE TO 
DEFEND MYSELF,

102
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:57,653
BUT FOR YOUR INFORMATION, 
I DID GO SHOPPING.

103
00:03:57,653 --> 00:04:00,448
- YOU SPENT $68 
ON HAIR CONDITIONER?

104
00:04:00,448 --> 00:04:03,158
- A SMALL PRICE TO PAY 
FOR SELF-ESTEEM, MICHAEL.

105
00:04:03,158 --> 00:04:05,745
OR ARE YOU STILL JEALOUS 
THAT YOU LOST "BEST HAIR" TO ME

106
00:04:05,745 --> 00:04:07,497
IN HIGH SCHOOL AND GOT DORKIEST?

107
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,582
- narrator: LINDSAY'S 
ACHIEVEMENTS IN HIGH SCHOOL

108
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:13,294
HAD ALWAYS OVERSHADOWED 
MICHAEL'S.

109
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:14,504
- I AGREE WITH MICHAEL.

110
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,381
IT'S IMPORTANT NOT TO TIE 
YOUR SELF-ESTEEM

111
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:18,841
INTO HOW YOU LOOK 
OR WHAT PEOPLE THINK OF YOU.

112
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:21,218
I MEAN, LOOK AT ME. 
I'M AN ACTOR,

113
00:04:21,218 --> 00:04:23,304
AN ACTOR FOR CRYING OUT LOUD.

114
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:27,850
I MEAN, YOU KNOW HOW MUCH 
REJECTION I FACE EVERY DAY?

115
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,395
BUT IN THIS BUSINESS OF SHOW,

116
00:04:30,395 --> 00:04:32,938
YOU HAVE TO HAVE THE HEART 
OF AN ANGEL

117
00:04:32,938 --> 00:04:36,276
AND THE HIDE OF AN ELEPHANT.

118
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:38,361
- BUT YOU'VE NEVER ACTUALLY HAD 
AN AUDITION.

119
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:42,282
- [chuckles] 
WELL...

120
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:46,160
[imitating Steve Martin] 
EXCUSE ME.

121
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,707
EXCUSE ME.

122
00:04:51,707 --> 00:04:53,418
- SOME REALLY GREAT 
SPOUSAL SUPPORT.

123
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:54,835
YOU KNOW SOMETHING, LINDSAY?

124
00:04:54,835 --> 00:04:56,421
YOU MIGHT WANNA START THINKING 
ABOUT THE EXAMPLE

125
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:57,672
YOU'RE SETTING 
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER,

126
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,965
UNLESS YOU WANT HER TO END UP 
JUST LIKE YOU.

127
00:04:59,965 --> 00:05:02,468
- YEAH, 
SHOOT ME WHEN THAT HAPPENS.

128
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:05,846
- IS THERE A CARBON MONOXIDE 
LEAK IN THIS HOUSE?

129
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:11,143
GEORGE MICHAEL, YOU'RE TAKING 
YOUR COUSIN TO WORK TODAY.

130
00:05:11,143 --> 00:05:12,312
THAT'S YOUR NEW EMPLOYEE.

131
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:13,688
I DO NOT WANT MY NIECE TO END UP

132
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:14,814
JUST LIKE EVERYONE 
IN THIS FAMILY.

133
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,441
- UH-UH, YOU'RE NOT TELLING 
MY DAUGHTER WHAT TO DO.

134
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:17,650
SHE'S A CHILD.

135
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,068
- NO, I'M NOT.

136
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:20,861
I CAN WORK.

137
00:05:20,861 --> 00:05:22,029
- I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THIS.

138
00:05:22,029 --> 00:05:24,699
I MEAN, IT CAN GET PRETTY HAIRY 
IN THERE, AND--

139
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:26,617
- FINE. 
DO WHAT YOU WANT.

140
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:29,745
IF I KNOW MY DAUGHTER, THAT 
STAND WON'T BE THERE IN A WEEK.

141
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,958
- YOU STAY ON TOP OF HER, BUDDY.

142
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:38,087
DO NOT BE AFRAID TO RIDE HER... 
HARD.

143
00:05:42,508 --> 00:05:44,719
narrator: GEORGE MICHAEL'S 
ATTEMPT TO DISTANCE HIMSELF

144
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:49,348
FROM HIS COUSIN 
PROVED UNSUCCESSFUL.

145
00:05:53,227 --> 00:05:54,520
- I CAN'T TELL YOU 
HOW MANY HEALTH CODES

146
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,063
YOU'RE VIOLATING RIGHT NOW.

147
00:05:56,063 --> 00:05:58,107
- I CAN'T BELIEVE I VOLUNTEERED 
FOR THIS.

148
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:01,569
THIS IS MY STUPIDEST 
REBELLION EVER.

149
00:06:01,569 --> 00:06:04,489
HEY, DO YOU WANNA GO PLAY 
SKEE-BALL?

150
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:05,740
- [coins jingling]

151
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,117
- WAIT... 
THIS IS THE CASH DRAWER.

152
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:09,619
MY DAD'S GONNA COME BY 
AT THE END OF THE WEEKEND,

153
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,120
AND THE NUMBER OF BANANAS 
HAS TO MATCH

154
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,121
THE AMOUNT OF MONEY IN HERE.

155
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:13,664
- OH, 
SO IT ALL HAS TO EVEN OUT?

156
00:06:13,664 --> 00:06:14,749
- EXACTLY.

157
00:06:14,749 --> 00:06:19,754
- EASY, 
BANANA...BUCK,

158
00:06:19,754 --> 00:06:22,923
BANANA...TAKE A BUCK.

159
00:06:22,923 --> 00:06:24,717
narrator: 
AND MICHAEL WENT TO HIS MOTHER

160
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:28,012
FOR THE FLIGHT RECORDS 
HIS FATHER WOULDN'T GIVE HIM.

161
00:06:28,012 --> 00:06:32,182
- THEN WHY DON'T YOU MARRY 
AN ICE CREAM SANDWICH?

162
00:06:32,182 --> 00:06:33,518
- I GOTTA GO.

163
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:34,852
- WHO WAS THAT? 
WAS THAT DAD?

164
00:06:34,852 --> 00:06:36,353
- THAT WAS GOB.

165
00:06:36,353 --> 00:06:37,855
- UH-HUH.

166
00:06:37,855 --> 00:06:39,231
SO, MOM, I'M TRYING TO FIND...

167
00:06:39,231 --> 00:06:40,441
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE THEY ARE.

168
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,902
- THESE FLIGHT RECORDS.

169
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:45,237
YOU KNOW, IT'S REALLY MORE 
BELIEVABLE IF YOU LET ME FINISH.

170
00:06:45,237 --> 00:06:46,489
WHY AM I THE ONLY ONE 
THAT SEEMS TO GET

171
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:48,491
HOW MUCH TROUBLE 
THIS FAMILY IS IN?

172
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:49,825
- OH, I GET IT, MICHAEL.

173
00:06:49,825 --> 00:06:51,410
I GET IT.

174
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,912
BUT HOW SHOULD I KNOW 
WHERE THE RECORDS ARE KEPT?

175
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,622
YOUR FATHER'S IN CHARGE 
OF ALL THAT.

176
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:56,624
- NO, I'M IN CHARGE 
OF ALL OF THAT.

177
00:06:56,624 --> 00:06:58,668
AND I THINK THAT YOU DO KNOW 
WHERE THEY ARE.

178
00:06:58,668 --> 00:07:01,629
- OH, IT'S PROBABLY ALL 
IN A STORAGE UNIT SOMEWHERE.

179
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:03,380
- WHERE IS THE STORAGE UNIT?

180
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:05,591
- I DON'T REMEMBER. 
- TRY.

181
00:07:05,591 --> 00:07:07,552
- SOMETHING WITH "DALE."

182
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,554
I DON'T KNOW, BROOKFEATHER. 
RAINTREE.

183
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,972
IT'S HOT. 
IT'S VERY HOT THERE.

184
00:07:11,972 --> 00:07:13,390
I'VE NEVER BEEN. 
GET A WARRANT.

185
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:15,935
- DON'T THINK I WON'T.

186
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,604
MOTHER,  MOTHER, 
I CARE ABOUT THIS FAMILY.

187
00:07:18,604 --> 00:07:21,441
- AND I DO TOO, MY DARLING.

188
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,233
THAT'S WHY I'M WORRIED 
ABOUT GOB.

189
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:24,694
I WAS ON THE PHONE WITH HIM 
THIS MORNING.

190
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:28,614
- YOU MEAN, JUST NOW, RIGHT, 
WHEN I CAME IN?

191
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:30,491
- YES, JUST NOW, 
WHEN YOU CAME IN.

192
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:31,909
AND HE'S UPSET.

193
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:33,035
HE'S VERY UPSET.

194
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:35,663
- YOU HAVEN'T INCLUDED HIM 
IN THE BUSINESS AT ALL.

195
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,914
- HE'S YOUR OLDER BROTHER.

196
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:38,666
YOU COULD FIND A LITTLE JOB 
FOR HIM.

197
00:07:38,666 --> 00:07:40,042
MAKE HIM FEEL SPECIAL.

198
00:07:40,042 --> 00:07:42,294
- BUT HE'S NOT SPECIAL, MOTHER.

199
00:07:42,294 --> 00:07:44,630
- NO.

200
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,507
BUT HE LOVES YOU.

201
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:48,342
WE ALL LOVE YOU.

202
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:49,802
- WHERE'S THE STORAGE UNIT?

203
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:51,471
- IT'S WITH YOUR WARRANT.

204
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,888
- [chuckling]

205
00:07:52,888 --> 00:07:57,392
LUZ, THAT COAT COST MORE 
THAN YOUR HOUSE.

206
00:07:57,392 --> 00:07:58,936
OH, THAT'S HOW WE JOKE.

207
00:07:58,936 --> 00:08:00,855
SHE DOESN'T EVEN HAVE A HOUSE.

208
00:08:03,232 --> 00:08:06,318
narrator: THE NEXT DAY, 
TOBIAS LOOKED FOR WORK.

209
00:08:06,318 --> 00:08:08,237
- HMM, ACTOR PULL.

210
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:16,829
OOH.

211
00:08:16,829 --> 00:08:19,540
OH, LOOK AT ALL THESE PARTS.

212
00:08:23,043 --> 00:08:25,170
- TOBIAS, 
NICE TO SEE YOU OFF THE COUCH.

213
00:08:25,170 --> 00:08:29,509
- I WAS LOOKING FOR WORK, 
AND I BLEW IT, MICHAEL.

214
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:32,136
- I GUESS YOU'VE ALREADY 
SEEN THAT, HUH?

215
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:33,888
- YES, I HAVE.

216
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,472
OH, RIGHT, THIS ONE.

217
00:08:35,472 --> 00:08:37,975
YEAH, I'LL CALL THEM AGAIN, 
I GUESS.

218
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:40,394
I'LL GIVE THEM ONE MORE SHOT.

219
00:08:40,394 --> 00:08:41,979
narrator: AND THAT'S 
WHEN MICHAEL FIGURED OUT

220
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:43,689
HOW TO GET HIS MOTHER 
TO LEAD HIM

221
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:46,859
TO THE STORAGE UNIT WHERE 
THE FLIGHT RECORDS WERE KEPT.

222
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:49,361
[cell phone rings]

223
00:08:49,361 --> 00:08:51,488
- HELLO. 
- HEY, MOM, IT'S MICHAEL.

224
00:08:51,488 --> 00:08:53,866
LISTEN, BEFORE I FORGET, 
I TALKED TO THE I.R.S.,

225
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,993
AND THEY WANNA COME BY 
YOUR APARTMENT TODAY

226
00:08:55,993 --> 00:08:58,996
TO SEE IF YOU CHARGED ANY 
BIG-TICKET STUFF TO THE COMPANY,

227
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:03,125
FURS OR...I DON'T KNOW.

228
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,544
JUST A HEADS-UP.

229
00:09:07,379 --> 00:09:09,632
OH, THAT POOR WOMAN.

230
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:14,219
narrator: 
SO MICHAEL FOLLOWED LUZ,

231
00:09:14,219 --> 00:09:16,639
WHO HAD BEEN SENT TO HIDE 
THE EVIDENCE.

232
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,724
MEANWHILE, 
TOBIAS HAD ARRANGED AN AUDITION

233
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:20,184
FOR A LOCAL COMMERCIAL.

234
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:22,477
LINDSAY CAME ALONG 
TO APPEAR SUPPORTIVE.

235
00:09:22,477 --> 00:09:24,104
- THIS COULD TAKE A WHILE.

236
00:09:24,104 --> 00:09:26,231
- HONEY, IT'S ONE LINE.

237
00:09:26,231 --> 00:09:28,651
- NOT IF I DO MY JOB RIGHT.

238
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:31,361
FIRST OF ALL, I LOVE IT.

239
00:09:31,361 --> 00:09:32,362
QUICK QUESTION, THOUGH.

240
00:09:32,362 --> 00:09:34,657
AM I PANICKED ABOUT THE FIRE,

241
00:09:34,657 --> 00:09:37,201
OR AM I BEING BRAVE 
FOR EVERYONE ELSE?

242
00:09:37,201 --> 00:09:41,205
- THE FIRE...IT'S... 
IT'S A FIRE SALE.

243
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:46,376
- OH.

244
00:09:46,376 --> 00:09:48,503
OKAY, I DIDN'T, UM...

245
00:09:48,503 --> 00:09:52,174
WELL, LET'S GIVE IT A SHOT.

246
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:53,843
OH, MY GOD.

247
00:09:53,843 --> 00:09:56,762
WE'RE HAVING A FIRE...SALE.

248
00:09:56,762 --> 00:09:58,347
OH, THE BURNING.

249
00:09:58,347 --> 00:10:00,182
IT BURNS ME.

250
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:02,602
EVACUATE ALL 
SCHOOLCHILDREN.

251
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:03,728
[screaming]

252
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:05,813
[singing] 
AMAAAA...

253
00:10:05,813 --> 00:10:07,022
THIS ISN'T A FEVER.

254
00:10:07,022 --> 00:10:08,774
[singing] 
ZING GRACE.

255
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:10,610
I CAN'T EVEN SEE 
WHERE THE KNOB IS.

256
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:21,078
AND SCENE.

257
00:10:21,078 --> 00:10:24,081
- UM...

258
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:27,167
WOULD YOU LIKE TO TRY THAT 
A LITTLE SIMPLER, MAYBE?

259
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,631
- NO.

260
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,384
- OKAY, ANYBODY ELSE?

261
00:10:35,384 --> 00:10:37,803
ANYONE?

262
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,680
LINDSAY BLUTH?

263
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,681
- IT'S FUNKE.

264
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:41,724
- ROGER DANISH.

265
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:42,975
- LOOK AT YOU.

266
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:44,184
I CAN'T BELIEVE 
IT'S LINDSAY BLUTH.

267
00:10:44,184 --> 00:10:45,770
- OH. 
- FUNKE.

268
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:49,815
- ROGER WAS MY MALE COUNTERPART 
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

269
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:52,151
- REMEMBER HOW CRAZY 
OUR HAIR WAS BACK THEN?

270
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,653
- WHAT WERE WE THINKING?

271
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,029
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING NOW?

272
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:57,031
- HE'S, UH, 
CASTING MY COMMERCIAL.

273
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:58,448
- YEAH, TRYING TO.

274
00:10:58,448 --> 00:11:00,826
THE SOUTH COAST BOUTIQUE 
IS HAVING A FIRE SALE.

275
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:02,703
- SOUTH COAST BOUTIQUE?

276
00:11:02,703 --> 00:11:04,496
THEY'RE HAVING A FIRE SALE?

277
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:11,378
narrator: MEANWHILE, 
MICHAEL WAS STILL FOLLOWING

278
00:11:11,378 --> 00:11:15,632
HIS MOTHER'S HOUSEKEEPER.

279
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:22,514
AND SHE DID FINALLY LEAD HIM 
TO THE STORAGE UNIT.

280
00:11:22,514 --> 00:11:25,976
UNFORTUNATELY, 
IT WAS ON FIRE.

281
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,483
- SOMEBODY WANTED THIS PLACE 
TO GO.

282
00:11:33,483 --> 00:11:35,069
- YEAH? 
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, ARSON?

283
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:38,072
- OH, DEFINITELY THE WORK 
OF A FLAMER.

284
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:55,840
- [shouting indistinctly]

285
00:11:59,343 --> 00:12:02,679
- IT SHOOTS TOMORROW, 
AND ARE YOU READY FOR THIS?

286
00:12:02,679 --> 00:12:05,891
IT PAYS 1,000 BUCKS.

287
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,726
- MM, 
I THOUGHT THAT WAS TOBIAS' PART.

288
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,979
- YES 
NO, NO, I DID NOT BOOK THIS ONE.

289
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,939
I, UH... 
I THINK I MADE THE, UH,

290
00:12:11,939 --> 00:12:14,524
FIRE TOO REAL, UH, FOR THEM, 
AND, UH...

291
00:12:14,524 --> 00:12:17,027
AND PROBABLY FAILED 
TO HIGHLIGHT THE SALE,

292
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:19,488
SO GOOD FOR HER, AND, UH,

293
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:21,281
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME, PLEASE?

294
00:12:21,281 --> 00:12:23,158
[chuckling]

295
00:12:23,158 --> 00:12:26,578
- WELL, THAT'S GREAT, 
BUT I'VE GOT MY OWN PROBLEMS.

296
00:12:26,578 --> 00:12:28,747
THE FLIGHT RECORDS, 
THEY'VE BURNED UP.

297
00:12:28,747 --> 00:12:30,374
THAT'S FINE. 
THAT'S OVER WITH.

298
00:12:30,374 --> 00:12:32,793
BUT I THINK DAD IS BEHIND IT.

299
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:35,587
I THINK DAD IS TRYING TO RUN 
THE BUSINESS FROM PRISON.

300
00:12:35,587 --> 00:12:37,047
- WELL, ISN'T THAT IRONIC?

301
00:12:37,047 --> 00:12:39,008
I'M MAKING A FORTUNE 
AT MY NEW JOB,

302
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:41,676
AND YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE THE JOB 
YOU THOUGHT YOU DID.

303
00:12:41,676 --> 00:12:43,720
- BUT YOU DON'T HAVE A JOB. 
YOU'VE GOT A JOB OFFER.

304
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,514
ANYBODY CAN GET A JOB OFFER.

305
00:12:45,514 --> 00:12:49,684
- [sobbing]

306
00:12:49,684 --> 00:12:51,270
- SO I'M GONNA GO SEE DAD,

307
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:51,871
BECAUSE THIS IS MY BUSINESS 
TO RUN NOW.

308
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:57,442
- YOUR BUSINESS?

309
00:12:57,442 --> 00:12:59,611
- HEY, THERE YOU ARE, GOB.

310
00:12:59,611 --> 00:13:01,530
I HAVE BEEN LOOKING ALL OVER 
FOR YOU.

311
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:04,408
I COULD REALLY USE SOME HELP.

312
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:08,245
- WELL, 
I WAS GONNA RETURN THIS DOVE.

313
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:09,663
WHAT ARE YOU...

314
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:11,623
YOU WANT ME TO RUN A MEETING 
FOR YOU OR SOMETHING?

315
00:13:11,623 --> 00:13:14,584
- OR EVEN BETTER, COULD YOU MAIL 
THIS LETTER FOR ME?

316
00:13:14,584 --> 00:13:17,421
- YOU CAN'T JUST GIVE THAT 
TO A MAILMAN?

317
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:19,924
- I CAN'T TRUST A MAILMAN 
WITH THIS.

318
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:21,008
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

319
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:22,467
narrator: 
GOB WAS INTRIGUED.

320
00:13:22,467 --> 00:13:24,553
HE ALSO SUSPECTED 
HE COULDN'T RETURN

321
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:26,513
A COMPLETELY FROZEN DOVE 
TO A PET STORE

322
00:13:26,513 --> 00:13:29,183
AND GET THE FULL REFUND HE FELT 
HE WAS ENTITLED TO.

323
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:31,060
- I'LL MAIL THAT LETTER.

324
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,812
narrator: MICHAEL THEN WENT 
TO CONFRONT HIS FATHER.

325
00:13:33,812 --> 00:13:36,023
- YOU ARE NOT GOING TO KEEP 
RUNNING THE COMPANY

326
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:37,816
FROM IN HERE, OKAY?

327
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:39,484
THAT'S WHY YOU WANTED ME 
TO GIVE T-BONE A JOB,

328
00:13:39,484 --> 00:13:41,320
TO PAY HIM BACK FOR BURNING DOWN 
THE STORAGE UNIT?

329
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,988
- MICHAEL, THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

330
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:44,781
- WELL, I'M NOT HIRING HIM.

331
00:13:44,781 --> 00:13:46,491
NO. 
WE DON'T HAVE THE MONEY, POP.

332
00:13:46,491 --> 00:13:49,203
- THERE'S ALWAYS MONEY 
IN THE BANANA STAND.

333
00:13:49,203 --> 00:13:50,662
- THE BANANA STAND.

334
00:13:50,662 --> 00:13:54,041
YOU KNOW, THAT'S EXACTLY 
WHAT THIS FEELS LIKE, HUH,

335
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:56,085
LIKE I'M STILL STUCK 
IN THAT HOT BOOTH ALL SUMMER

336
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,127
WITH YOU PULLING THE STRINGS.

337
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,337
- WHAT WAS I GONNA DO, 
PUT A KID

338
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:00,255
IN CHARGE 
OF A FROZEN BANANA STAND?

339
00:14:00,255 --> 00:14:01,381
- SURE. 
THAT'S WHAT I DID.

340
00:14:01,381 --> 00:14:03,926
I JUST MADE MY SON THE MANAGER.

341
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:06,971
- GEORGE MICHAEL IS RUNNING 
THE FROZEN BANANA STAND NOW?

342
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,722
- THAT'S RIGHT, YEAH. 
YOU SIT WITH THAT.

343
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:11,058
YOU THINK ABOUT THAT 
FOR A WHILE.

344
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:14,686
narrator: GEORGE SR. DID THINK 
ABOUT THAT.

345
00:14:17,397 --> 00:14:21,568
- WELL, NOW THAT WE'VE GOT AN 
EMPLOYEE, WE CAN GO HAVE DINNER.

346
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:26,198
WE THROW AWAY A BANANA 
FOR EVERY BUCK WE TAKE

347
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:28,200
SO NO ONE FINDS OUT.

348
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,702
- WAIT A MINUTE; I THINK YOU 
SHOULD DO THAT MATH AGAIN.

349
00:14:30,702 --> 00:14:32,454
- WHY? 
IS IT WRONG?

350
00:14:32,454 --> 00:14:33,663
- IT'S FINE.

351
00:14:33,663 --> 00:14:35,540
- HE'S AN ARSONIST, 
NOT AN EMBEZZLER.

352
00:14:37,292 --> 00:14:40,504
narrator: MEANWHILE, MICHAEL GOT 
AN URGENT CALL FROM HIS MOTHER.

353
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:42,839
- GOB IS UNHAPPY.

354
00:14:42,839 --> 00:14:44,424
- AGAIN? 
I TRIED TO INCLUDE HIM.

355
00:14:44,424 --> 00:14:45,550
I GAVE HIM A JOB.

356
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:47,261
- YOU GAVE HIM A LETTER TO MAIL.

357
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:49,138
- DON'T TELL ME THAT WAS 
TOO MUCH FOR HIM.

358
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:51,015
- NO, MICHAEL. 
HE MAILED THE LETTER.

359
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:52,474
THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

360
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:54,059
narrator: 
GOB HAD NOT MAILED THE LETTER,

361
00:14:54,059 --> 00:14:55,644
BUT IN AN ACT OF DEFIANCE

362
00:14:55,644 --> 00:15:00,274
DRAMATICALLY HURLED THE LETTER 
INTO THE SEA.

363
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:03,068
THIS PROVED A MORE DIFFICULT 
DRAMATIC GESTURE

364
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:06,405
THAN HE'D ANTICIPATED.

365
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:12,411
- [singing breezy, 
latin-tinged music]

366
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,333
- SO WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO 
ABOUT IT?

367
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,459
- DON'T TAKE THAT TONE.

368
00:15:19,459 --> 00:15:20,627
- HE'S MY SON.

369
00:15:20,627 --> 00:15:22,922
I WANT YOU TO MAKE HIM 
STOP CALLING ME.

370
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:24,256
[door clicks open]

371
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:26,258
- AM I THE ONLY ONE WHO WORKS 
IN THIS FAMILY?

372
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:29,594
- [chuckling] 
YES, THAT'S MY GAL.

373
00:15:29,594 --> 00:15:32,973
WHO WOULD HAVE IMAGINED 
TWO ACTORS IN ONE FAMILY?

374
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:35,892
WE'RE LIKE THE LUNTS.

375
00:15:35,892 --> 00:15:40,230
YOU SEE...EXCUSE ME.

376
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,941
- MAMA. 
- muah!

377
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:44,318
narrator: AND SO LINDSAY 
AND MAEBY SEPARATELY WENT

378
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,361
TO THE SAME RESTAURANT 
TO CELEBRATE THE JOBS

379
00:15:46,361 --> 00:15:48,113
THEY HADN'T 
ACTUALLY PERFORMED

380
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:50,950
WITH MONEY THEY HADN'T 
ACTUALLY EARNED.

381
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,118
- DID YOU ENJOY YOUR MEAL, MOM?' 
YOU DRANK IT FAST ENOUGH.

382
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:54,328
- HI, LUCILLE.

383
00:15:54,328 --> 00:15:56,288
- NOT AS MUCH AS YOU 
ENJOYED YOURS.

384
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:58,707
YOU WANT YOUR BELT TO BUCKLE, 
NOT YOUR CHAIR.

385
00:15:58,707 --> 00:16:01,543
- OKAY, THIS IS WHAT I TOLD 
TOBIAS YOU'D DO.

386
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:02,669
SAY WHAT YOU WILL ABOUT HIM.

387
00:16:02,669 --> 00:16:04,713
AT LEAST HE'S HAPPY FOR ME.

388
00:16:04,713 --> 00:16:08,717
- [sobbing]

389
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:12,221
- YOU KNOW, I THINK WE MIGHT BE 
DOUBLING OUR LOSSES HERE.

390
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:14,098
BECAUSE, I MEAN, 
FOR EVERY DOLLAR YOU TAKE,

391
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:16,183
WE'RE ACTUALLY TAKING 
TWO DOLLARS,

392
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:18,978
BECAUSE WE PAID FOR THE BANANAS.

393
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:21,105
- [chuckles] 
OH, MY GOD, YOU'RE RIGHT.

394
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:22,689
- I AM?

395
00:16:22,689 --> 00:16:24,774
OH, GOD, I'VE SCREWED THIS UP.

396
00:16:24,774 --> 00:16:26,693
OKAY, WE GOTTA GO.

397
00:16:26,693 --> 00:16:27,861
OH, MY GOD.

398
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:29,821
IT'S YOUR MOM AND GANGY.

399
00:16:29,821 --> 00:16:31,531
- WHAT ARE THEY DOING HERE? 
- THEY'RE GROWN-UPS.

400
00:16:31,531 --> 00:16:33,075
THEY'RE ALLOWED TO HAVE FUN 
WHENEVER THEY WANT.

401
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:34,659
WE'RE KIDS. 
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE WORKING.

402
00:16:34,659 --> 00:16:36,286
NOW THEY'RE GONNA TELL MY DAD,

403
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:37,537
AND HE'S GONNA COME CHECK 
THE TOTALS AND KNOW

404
00:16:37,537 --> 00:16:38,913
WE TOOK THE MONEY.

405
00:16:38,913 --> 00:16:40,207
OH, GOD, THIS IS BAD.

406
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,458
- LOOK... 
- WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

407
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,418
- POP-POP, 
HE'S A BUSINESS MAN.

408
00:16:43,418 --> 00:16:46,046
WHAT WOULD HE DO?

409
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:49,383
- BANANAS FOSTER.

410
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,346
- YOU MIGHT WANNA LET 
THAT FIRE GO OUT

411
00:16:54,346 --> 00:16:55,597
BEFORE YOU STICK YOUR FACE 
IN IT.

412
00:16:55,597 --> 00:16:56,890
- THAT'S FUNNY, 
'CAUSE I WAS GONNA SAY,

413
00:16:56,890 --> 00:16:58,433
"YOU MIGHT WANNA LEAN AWAY 
FROM THAT FIRE

414
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:00,435
SINCE YOU'RE SOAKED IN ALCOHOL."

415
00:17:00,435 --> 00:17:03,480
- MINE WAS BETTER.

416
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,441
- WELCOME TO BLUTH BANANAS, 
WHERE BANANAS ARE OUR BUSINESS.

417
00:17:06,441 --> 00:17:08,527
MAY I INTEREST YOU IN A BANANA 
THIS DAY?

418
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:10,070
- T-BONE, 
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

419
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:12,614
- OH, YOUR DAD GAVE ME THIS JOB.

420
00:17:12,614 --> 00:17:14,866
narrator: MICHAEL REALIZED 
THAT HIS FATHER

421
00:17:14,866 --> 00:17:17,994
HAD EVEN TAKEN CONTROL 
OF THE BANANA STAND,

422
00:17:17,994 --> 00:17:20,080
BUT HE STILL HAD 
SOME UNANSWERED QUESTIONS,

423
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,248
SO HE DID 
A LITTLE DETECTIVE WORK.

424
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:23,250
- YOU BURN DOWN 
THE STORAGE UNIT?

425
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,960
- OH, MOST DEFINITELY.

426
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:32,217
- MICHAEL, HAVING A NICE DAY 
AT THE BEACH,

427
00:17:32,217 --> 00:17:35,637
WHILE THE REST OF US ARE BUSTING 
OUR ASSES TO DELIVER YOUR MAIL?

428
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:37,764
- WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO SAY, 
OKAY?

429
00:17:37,764 --> 00:17:40,142
YOU GO AND COMPLAIN TO MOM, 
AND I TRIED TO INCLUDE YOU.

430
00:17:40,142 --> 00:17:41,393
- INCLUDE ME? 
- YEAH.

431
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,727
- I SHOULD BE IN CHARGE.

432
00:17:42,727 --> 00:17:43,978
I'M THE OLDER BROTHER.

433
00:17:43,978 --> 00:17:45,105
- PLEASE, DO YOU EVEN WANT 
TO BE IN CHARGE?

434
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:48,608
- NO, 
BUT I'D LIKE TO BE ASKED.

435
00:17:48,608 --> 00:17:49,693
THIS IS JUST LIKE 
WHEN WE WERE KIDS,

436
00:17:49,693 --> 00:17:52,237
AND YOU WERE THE ONLY ONE 
HE LET WORK IN THE BANANA STAND.

437
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:54,156
- WELL, I GOT NEWS FOR YOU, GOB,

438
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,865
DAD STILL DOESN'T TRUST ME 
TO THIS DAY.

439
00:17:55,865 --> 00:17:57,492
HE TREATS ME LIKE 
A LOW-LEVEL EMPLOYEE.

440
00:17:57,492 --> 00:18:00,245
- BETTER THAN BEING TREATED 
LIKE THE GOOFBALL,

441
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:03,457
THE JOKER, 
THE MAGICIAN.

442
00:18:05,709 --> 00:18:07,252
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA DO, 
LIKE, A TRICK THERE,

443
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:08,545
LIKE THE FIREBALL OR SOMETHING.

444
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:09,588
- I WAS. 
IT DIDN'T GO OFF.

445
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:11,506
- THESE THINGS NEVER GO OFF 
WHEN YOU WANT THEM TO,

446
00:18:11,506 --> 00:18:12,674
MY LEAST-CONSISTENT TRICK.

447
00:18:12,674 --> 00:18:14,343
- HANG ON ONE SEC. 
- HELLO.

448
00:18:14,343 --> 00:18:15,927
- HEY, UNCLE MICHAEL, 
IT'S ME, MAEBY.

449
00:18:15,927 --> 00:18:17,137
- HEY, MAEBY, 
WHERE'S GEORGE MICHAEL?

450
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,472
- AT THE BANANA STAND.

451
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:22,226
HE'S ABOUT TO DO SOMETHING 
REALLY IRRESPONSIBLE.

452
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:23,727
- YOU THINK IT'S IRRESPONSIBLE?

453
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:26,438
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

454
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:28,107
- I'M GONNA GET BLAMED FOR THIS.

455
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:29,941
- GEORGE MICHAEL. 
- DAD.

456
00:18:29,941 --> 00:18:31,735
- HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

457
00:18:31,735 --> 00:18:34,738
- I WAS JUST, UH...

458
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,698
I WAS BURNING DOWN 
THE BANANA STAND.

459
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:37,991
- WHAT? 
- I'M SORRY, DAD.

460
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:39,409
I SCREWED IT ALL UP.

461
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:41,536
I'VE GOT NO RIGHT TO CALL MYSELF 
MR. MANAGER.

462
00:18:41,536 --> 00:18:42,829
- MANAGER. 
- MANAGER.

463
00:18:42,829 --> 00:18:44,414
- I'M SORRY, DAD. 
- OH, GEORGE MICHAEL.

464
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:46,541
- I AM, 
BUT I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

465
00:18:46,541 --> 00:18:48,502
I'LL WORK WEEKNIGHTS. 
I'LL LAY PEOPLE OFF.

466
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:50,379
I'LL GIVE UP MY SUMMER, 
ALL MY SUMMERS.

467
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,547
JUST TELL ME WHAT TO DO, 
AND I'LL DO IT.

468
00:18:52,547 --> 00:18:54,299
narrator: MICHAEL REALIZED HE 
HAD DONE TO HIS SON

469
00:18:54,299 --> 00:18:56,885
WHAT HIS FATHER HAD DONE 
TO HIM,

470
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:59,179
SO HE CAME UP WITH A SOLUTION.

471
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:00,847
- BURN IT DOWN.

472
00:19:00,847 --> 00:19:02,641
- WHAT?

473
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:07,020
- LET'S BURN 
THIS SON OF A BITCH.

474
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:19,032
- THIS IS GONNA BE 
OUR BEST SUMMER EVER, BUDDY.

475
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:23,828
narrator: AND SO, MICHAEL, 
HIS SON,

476
00:19:23,828 --> 00:19:25,997
AND HIS BROTHER 
TOGETHER ENJOYED

477
00:19:25,997 --> 00:19:28,917
THE CATHARTIC BURNING 
OF THE BANANA STAND.

478
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:32,086
YOU MAILED THAT INSURANCE CHECK, 
RIGHT, GOB?

479
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:37,133
- [singing] 
AND WE'VE BEEN TAKIN' CARE

480
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,803
OF BUSINESS EVERY DAY

481
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:43,014
TAKIN' CARE OF BUSINESS 
EVERY WAY

482
00:19:43,014 --> 00:19:45,850
WE'VE BEEN TAKIN' CARE 
OF BUSINESS

483
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:47,060
IT'S ALL RIGHT

484
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:49,354
narrator: THE NEXT MORNING, 
LINDSAY WOKE UP LATE IN THE DAY

485
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:51,731
HUNGOVER FROM CELEBRATING 
HER ONE DAY OF EMPLOYMENT,

486
00:19:51,731 --> 00:19:54,234
WHICH, IT TURNS OUT, 
SHE HAD SLEPT THROUGH.

487
00:19:54,234 --> 00:19:55,819
- ALL RIGHT, LINDSAY, FORGET IT.

488
00:19:55,819 --> 00:19:57,237
WE'LL GET SOMEONE ELSE.

489
00:19:57,237 --> 00:19:59,113
narrator: TOBIAS WAS NEXT 
ON THE CALL LIST,

490
00:19:59,113 --> 00:20:01,115
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY, 
COULDN'T HEAR THE PHONE

491
00:20:01,115 --> 00:20:04,536
OVER THE SOUND OF THE SHOWER.

492
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:06,955
HE DID, HOWEVER, 
USE LINDSAY'S CONDITIONER

493
00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:10,209
AND WAS SURPRISED TO FIND THAT 
IT DID HELP HIS SELF-ESTEEM.

494
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:11,960
- MORNIN'. 
- YOU LOOK NICE.

495
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:13,086
- WHAT?

496
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:15,088
- YOU LOOK VERY HANDSOME TODAY.

497
00:20:15,088 --> 00:20:18,717
- THANK YOU, LINDSAY.

498
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:20,093
narrator: 
AND MICHAEL FINALLY GOT

499
00:20:20,093 --> 00:20:21,845
TO SHOW HIS FATHER WHO'S BOSS.

500
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:22,971
- YOU WHAT?

501
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,806
- BURNED IT RIGHT DOWN 
TO THE GROUND

502
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:26,391
- ARE YOU CRAZY?

503
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:28,352
THERE WAS MONEY 
IN THAT BANANA STAND.

504
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:31,187
- WELL, IT'S ALL GONE NOW, DAD, 
AND IT WAS MY DECISION.

505
00:20:31,187 --> 00:20:33,357
SO THE NEXT TIME YOU WANNA HAVE 
A LITTLE POWER STRUGGLE,

506
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:35,775
JUST REMEMBER 
THAT YOU'RE PLAYING WITH FIRE.

507
00:20:35,775 --> 00:20:40,447
- THERE WAS $250,000 LINING 
THE WALLS OF THE BANANA STAND.

508
00:20:40,447 --> 00:20:42,241
- WHAT?

509
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:43,825
- CASH, MICHAEL.

510
00:20:43,825 --> 00:20:44,993
- WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME THAT?

511
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:46,953
- HOW MUCH CLEARER CAN I SAY,

512
00:20:46,953 --> 00:20:50,707
"THERE'S ALWAYS MONEY 
IN THE BANANA STAND"?

513
00:20:50,707 --> 00:20:52,251
- NO TOUCHING. 
- NO TOUCHING.

514
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,252
- NO TOUCHING. 
- NO TOUCHING.

515
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,211
- NO TOUCHING. 
